data.title: 以 3 到 5 分钟描写以下主题
data.content: Name a time when you wanted something but could not have it. How did you feel about not getting it? What did you learn from this experience, and how will it help you in life?
data.answer: There was a time that I really wanted to have junk food but I could not. Because I was having some weight issues. Due to the past 12 months, I let myself eat whatever I wanted to eat and it included some very unhealthy choices, including junk food, cakes, sweets, and carbonated drinks. Last week, I decided to quit unhealthy food and started to participate in physical exercises every morning. Things went well for two days. However, after that, I started to crave all the unhealthy food. After going through a lot of pain, I finally decided to ignore my cravings and went for some exercise. I felt much better after the workout and I was proud of myself that I did not start to eat junk food again. I think I will keep up with my new routine because I believe that it could help me improve my overall health.
